  "@type": "SolutionRecord",
  "@id": "ocp:github/eleanorlutz--asteroids_atlas_of_space",
  "meta": {
    "title": "Mapping The Solar System",
    "description": "Code, data, and instructions for mapping orbits of asteroids in the solar system",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-11T04:44:56.695Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-11T04:44:56.695Z",
    "keywords": [
      "astronomy",
      "cartography",
      "dataviz",
      "orbit"
    ],
    "license": "GPL-3.0"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "[![License: GPL v3](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-GPL%20v3-blue.svg?style=flat-square)](https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0)\n[![GitHub Follow](https://img.shields.io/github/followers/eleanorlutz.svg?style=flat-square&logo=github&label=Follow)](https://github.com/eleanorlutz)",
    "context": "[![License: GPL v3](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-GPL%20v3-blue.svg?style=flat-square)](https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0)\n[![GitHub Follow](https://img.shields.io/github/followers/eleanorlutz.svg?style=flat-square&logo=github&label=Follow)](https://github.com/eleanorlutz)\n\nThis repository explains how to make a map of the solar system using open-source code and data from NASA. Software used includes `Python 3.7.1`, `NASA HORIZONS`, `Illustrator CC 2019` and `Photoshop CC 2019`. If you have comments or suggestions for this tutorial, please let me know [on my blog](http://tabletopwhale.com/2019/06/10/the-solar-system.html)! You can buy the [finished map here](https://www.redbubble.com/people/eleanorlutz/works/39373641-an-asteroid-map-of-the-solar-system).\n\n**Python dependencies:** `matplotlib` `astropy` `numpy` `pandas` `os` `time` `urllib`. Dependencies can be installed with `pip install -r requirements.txt`.\n\n![Snapshot of final product](./readme_figures/asteroids.jpg)",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
